article.headline: McNeese State holds off Stillman 81-72
article.story: TUSCALOOSA, Ala. -- Craig McFerrin had 20 points and 13 rebounds on Tuesday night to lead McNeese State over Stillman 81-72 in the South consolation game of the NIT Season Tip-Off. Kevin Hardy added 13 points and 13 rebounds and Ledrick Eackles had 18 points. The Cowboys (2-3) led only 52-48 with 12:10 to go but quickly pulled away and stayed comfortably ahead the rest of the way. McNeese State took its first lead of the game 28-27 on Keelan Garrett's layup with 4:20 to go in the first half. Stanley Magee was 4 of 5 from 3-point range for Stillman and finished with 19 points and 11 rebounds. Markeith Madison had 13 points and 11 rebounds and Daniel Bryant was 4 of 22 from the field and 2 of 13 from beyond the arc. Markeith Madison's 3-point jumper put Stillman ahead 19-10 with 12:08 to go in the first half.
